RACE.RACE_TEXT: ALBUQUERQUE RACE 1 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 60. Maiden Claiming Purse 15200. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $6,500.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: WHAT A MEMORY had good early speed then shuffled back around the half pole then was never far back from the leaders as they came around the turn made an outside bid and with a strong drive won the race. CORY LOVES RAIN ran at the front of the pack with maintained off pace from the leaders on the outside and continued that pace thru the wire. KATZIE BABY had a slight mild gain at the start of the race then with a good pace took the lead coming on to the stretch but then was caught late stretch within the last seventy five yards. TAMMY MACHO ran off pace from the leaders then on the stretch ducked into the rail and took the inside path to keep up with the leaders. MIDNIGHT SUSI ran with good speed early in the race then late into the turn and early stretch hung slightly shuffling back. MORATTA ran at the back of the pack then on the main stretch on the inside had a strong rally to pass some foes. LILY J got off slow at the break then waited to come on to the stretch to make a final kick to overtake foes. ALSONO'S HUNTER ran on the outside with an even pace throughout the race then down the main stretch in the six path on the outside. SHAME ON YOU ran with good speed at the start then at the three eights pole started to fall back then ended up fading back the remainder of the race. PERFECT MESA ran at the back of the pack then coming down the stretch hung and rode out the race. EXPECT CANDY ran in the middle of the pack then in the middle of the turn started to faded and slowed on the stretch. PARK IN THE DARK trailed throughout the race at the back of the pack then started to catch a tired foe close to the wire. THIS RACE WAS HAND TIMED.

ENTRY.NAME: Midnight Susi
ENTRY.OWNER: Medina Robert H and Medina Michael

ENTRY.NAME: What a Memory
ENTRY.COMMENT: early speed, shuffled back, strong closing outside drive

WINNERS_DETAILS.BREEDER: Ron Kirk, John Bates & Michael Riordan

ENTRY.COMMENT: off pace rail trip on stretch

RACE.RACE_TEXT: ALBUQUERQUE RACE 2 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 74. Claiming Purse 19100. FOR REGISTERED NEW MEXICO BRED THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since July 27 Allowed 3 lbs. Claiming Price $6,250 (Condition Eligibility Preferred).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: GOLDEN MERGER ran in the middle of the pack then on the turn made a rally and snuck in to the gap two wide coming out of the turn then made a strong driving effort and drew off from the pack. ABSTRACT KAT ran at the back of the pack then took the six path on the outside of the pack with a strong kick down the stretch to over take most of the foes in the race. MASTERCLASS ran on the outside at the front of the pack then took the corner five wide and maintained a even pace down the stretch. GAMBLING COWBOY ran in the middle of the pack and had a slight mild gain in pace on the stretch. MICKEYS GOLD ran off pace from the leaders going three wide around the turn then hung mid stretch. WATFORD ran at the back of the pack then late into the stretch started passing tired foes. M G M'S LUCKY set the early pace but was pressed by multiple foes and ended up fading mid stretch. D C ALLIED FORCES ran with early speed pressed the pace but it was too much and they faded at the start of the stretch. THIS RACE WAS HAND TIMED.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: ALBUQUERQUE RACE 3 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 105. Allowance Purse 36400. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON TWO RACES SINCE APRIL 27, 2023 OR WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE SINCE JULY 27, 2023. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: PRAYER OF JABEZ early on in the race they got out front and then slowly drew off from the rest of the pack and didnt need to be asked for more down the stretch. TULANE TRYST ran with a mild gain in pace throughout, was squeezed out at the start but made up ground throughout the race. CYBERVIKING ran in the middle of the pack then shuffled back on the turn then had a strong rally on the rail to pass the foes on the inside. GOOD BYE CHARLIE ran with good early speed then shuffled back late stretch. MINISTER OF SOUL ran at the back of the pack then had a slight gain on the turn but shuffled back again on the stretch but passed tired foes late stretch. GIANT'S BRITE EYE ran in the middle of the pack then at the start of the stretch hung and fell back. ROCKY BAR SIX ran at the front of the pack but the pace was too much and they faded back in the middle of the turn. THIS RACE WAS HAND TIMED.

ENTRY.NAME: Cyberviking
ENTRY.COMMENT: shuffled back on turn, rallied on rail

RACE.RACE_TEXT: ALBUQUERQUE RACE 4 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 87. Claiming Purse 16200. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON TWO RACES IN 2023 OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since July 27 Allowed 3 lbs. A Race In 2023 Allowed 5 lbs. Claiming Price $6,250. New Mexico Bred Claiming Price $8,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: HIT THE SEAM set the early pace then maintained a comfortable lead throughout the race and as the others rallied behind they held on for the win. COYSTER ran at the back of the pack then coming down the stretch took to the rail and had a strong rally to overtake foes and end in the place position. DISCREET TIGER ran with good early speed then then late into the race shuffled back slightly late stretch. BIG LEAGUE BENNY ran in the back of the pack on the outside then coming down the stretch took to the outside and passed foes. RHODIUM RUNNER ran in the middle of the pack with an even pace throughout the race. PATRIOT ran in the front of the pack then coming down the stretch by the sixteenth pole started to shuffle back. LIL LATIGO ran in the middle of the pack then at the start of the stretch started to hang with the pacing. GORDY'S RULES ran at the back of the pack then had a late kick along with passing tired foes. CRUMAN TAPOTE ran in the middle of the pack then mid stretch faded back. LEAD MONTEREY ran in the middle of the pack then at the start of the stretch started to fade back. FIGHT ME ran in the middle of the pack then faded mid turn to last by the stretch. THIS RACE WAS HAND TIMED. PER THE NEW MEXICO RACING COMMISSION, BIG LEAGUE BENNY HAS BEEN DQ'D FOR A POSITIVE TEST.

ENTRY.NAME: Hit the Seam
ENTRY.COMMENT: set the early pace, held on for win
